ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMER — SCIENTIFIC CALCULATIONS

Supercalc is provided for educational and advisory purposes only. The values it
produces — surface impedance, sheet kinetic inductance, single-spin density of
states N0, derived film parameters, and the stored material data — are
APPROXIMATE ESTIMATES from idealized models (e.g., the thin-film limit of
Zmuidzinas 2012 Eq. 8, with a BCS or user-supplied gap ratio) and from
literature values that are sample-, deposition-, and measurement-dependent.

These results are ADVISORY ONLY and carry NO WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, express or
implied, as to their accuracy, completeness, or fitness for any purpose. They
must not be relied upon as the sole basis for any design, fabrication,
procurement, safety, or financial decision. You are solely responsible for
independently verifying every result against primary references and your own
measurements before acting on it. Use is entirely at your own risk.
